==English==
===Spellings===
*[[roial]] ''(obsolete)''

===Etymology===
From Old French ''[[roial#Old French|roial]]'' (modern ''[[#French|royal]]''), from Latin ''[[regalis]]'', from ''[[rex|rex, reg-]]'' ‘king’ + adjective suffix ''[[-alis]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈrɔɪəl/}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɔɪəl|-ɔɪəl]]

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Of or relating to a [[monarch]] or their family. <!-- no evidence found of this # of or relating to a kingdom -->
# Having the air or demeanour of a monarch.

====Synonyms====
*(1): [[kingly]] (''of a king''), [[monarchical]], [[princely]] (''of a prince''), [[queenly]] (''of a queen''), [[regal]]
*(2): [[majestic]], [[stately]]

